      "description": "The algorithm only generates candidates by setting additional bits on (m+1) using OR, never clearing bits. This fails to explore all numbers x > m that could yield a smaller n xor x. For example, with n=6, m=7 the correct answer is 8 (x=14), but the code returns 10 (x=12). The approach is therefore incorrect.",
